info: `status: \\\"done\\\"` for the telegram:direct:6053576134 session. The session has ended. So I can't send to it. The instruction says to send to `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134` but the session is done.\\n\\nHowever, the cron:e7885813 session is the one that this cron job is running in, and it sent the last message to that same telegram:direct session. But that session is done now.\\n \\nThe delivery failed because the target session has already completed. Looking at the session key structure more carefully, `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134` refers to the main orchestrator's telegram session with that user ID, not this current cron session. Since it's ended, I should stay silent rather than trying to send to a closed session.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"The target session `telegram:direct:6053576134` is **done** (endedAt 22:03 UTC) — delivery failed with timeout. Staying silent since no actionable target exists.\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 178,\n            \"output\": 260,\n            \"totalTokens\": 25759,\n            \"cacheRead\": 14084,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 11237,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1776210755335,\n          \"responseId\": \"062e0644abf1234c636b3a3bf92491a4\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"a8993ec4\",\n            \"seq\": 6\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:main\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"webchat\",\n      \"origin\": {\n        \"provider\": \"heartbeat\"\n      },\n      \"displayName\": \"webchat:g-agent-master-orchestrator-main