ferent instance ba6b61c6 that started at 23:31 UTC - they must be separate runs of the same job.\n\nThe cron:e7885813 entry appears to be the same session I've been tracking all along, not something new. Comparing against the heartbeat-state baseline, the 5p QLHV Monitor was already running, and nothing has fundamentally changed since then.\n\nThe Agent Status cron completed and restarted as expected, the DTLX Monitor is cycling normally every 5 minutes, and the Telegram group session's status shifted from done to running, but that's likely just a metadata update rather than an actual restart. There are no new failures or blockers to report, so I'm going silent on this one.\n\nActually, I need to clarify the Telegram session situation. The heartbeat-state marked it as done at 21:49 UTC, but it's showing as running now with recent messages from the heartbeat window. That could mean either the status field wasn't updated properly, or the session actually restarted. Let me dig into the session details to figure out which one it is.\n\nThe session metadata shows `updatedAt: 1776207640198` (22:40 UTC) and the last message from the group came in at 22:55 UTC, which is still within the last hour. So this looks like the same session that's been running all along—the status field just wasn't updated. Even if it did restart, that's a lifecycle event without any failures or blockers, so there's nothing to report.\n\nNow I need to update the heartbeat-state.json to reflect the current time of 23:59 UTC, and I should also check whether the telegram:group session has actually restarted or if it's still the same one that's been running. I'm going to stay silent on this one — nothing has fundamentally changed from the baseline state, so there's nothing new to report.","thinkingSignature":"87b0589c77bfc30489a533b659244bc951ea6cbae7b619e9def657ded40f84ac"},{"type":"text","text":"Comparing current state (23:59 UTC) vs. baseline (23:34 UTC from heartbeat-state.json):\n\n| Session | Bas